value: Resident in northern North America from central Alaska, south- ern Mackenzie, northern Manitoba, James Bay, northern Quebec (Richmond Gulf) southern Labrador (Natashkwan River), Anti- costi Island and Newfoundland, south to the mountains of Cali- fornia (Siskyou and Warner Mountains), Cascade Range and the Sierra Nevada south to lat. 37Â° 30' N., western Nevada, north- western Wyoming, southwestern South Dakota, northern Min- nesota, northeastern Wisconsin and the upper peninsula of Michigan, southeastern Ontario (Muskoka district), the Adiron- dack Mountains, Green Mountains, White Mountains and northern Maine. Casual in winter south to Nebraska, Illinois, Indiana, Ohio, Pennsylvania and northern New Jersey.
